\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, I tell you - the only thing I'll tell you what I did - th
is young - this brother that's left now - we often have a blooming good laugh over it - er - I er - when he started school of course them days you started school at five - well I took him - I took him to school and I used to take him every morning and aft
e
rnoon, you see, - well sometimes he'd get a mad fit on. I'd just get him right inside the school passage and I'd be in my line for school - er - for to go in when all at once somebody'd say 'Kate, there's Richard running home' - and I'd have to run after 
him - he'd run out of the line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 He didn't like school at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No. And it - to this - he often says - sometimes when I'm kidding him 'Yes you devil you always led me a dance, haven't you'. And he always says 'I was a very good little boy when I was five'. But still .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes - eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Up to what age would you have gone to bed at eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Up to - oh up to - was about sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your mother, not when you were sixteen, but when you were younger, did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - Mother always took us to bed. Always took us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What age did you put yourself to bed? Can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well, I started 
to go to bed - er - pretty early when I came home from work - when I started work at fourteen. You see, you could - I left school on the Friday - I went to Sunday school on the Sunday afternoon and me class mate - was working - a couple of month - and she
 
said - we talk - and I said 'I'm fourteen, Louie. She said 'Well come down to our place in the morning' she said 'they're taking on girls.'. And I went and I started. Well when I come home at night of course I was feel - I had to get up at five o'clock ..
..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 So it was a long day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Yes because we had to - er - we had to be in work for seven - well I used to get up at five and then of course I was glad to get to bed sometimes after about seven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Ready for bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What age would you have said then that you put yourself to bed? When you were still at school? When your mother stopped putting you to bed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well, I'd say - when I was still at school - oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. My sister Cissie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And in a single bed or a double bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No - we had a double bed - we had a double bed and a single bed - but the single bed was in the front room in the big room for Elsie - the youngest girl. But the boys had the next room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 The boys had a room on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 The boys had a room - yes. The boys .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 There were seven of you weren't there or six because one boy had died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes - yes, well the boys - er - the boys had the next room - two boys had the next room 
and the other boy had the attic - while we were all lit - at home - growing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And you had a double bed with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And there was another single bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes - in mother's room for the other sister - for the youngest girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Your mother and father had a bedroom and they also had a bed for ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh yes - for Elsie - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Is this all being recorded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 It's all going down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Is it - ooh heck. What room d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 id we bath in? Well, mum bathed}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  - er - mum used to - er - make the boys stay out a little later on a Friday night and she bathed us girls first and then the boys after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And where would she have bathed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Back kitchen - in front -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 In front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes - well - we had a big boiler and - er - for the water and 'twas warm and the door was always kept jammed tight and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 So no one could burst in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - and for the warmth and then of course we after we had the bath there was always a nice drink of hot 
milk ready for us and right to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes that was our bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Mother bathed us every Friday night of our life. Every Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And when did you have clean }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 clothes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Every Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 This would be a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 A regular thing - every Sunday morning there was clean clothes and then mother washed on a Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 This was the middle room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 The middle room - parlour and kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room or did you always eat in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, always ate in the kitchen. 'Cos was a big kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 In the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And how did she cook - on what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well - no - we had the - er - a lovely big oven in the kitchen - and she done all the roasting and all that in the oven - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And did she ever get a gas fire or ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 A little gas ring - little gas ring - yes. 'course there wasn't the same style of cookers and that them days - as you'll know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 The lovely old oven and the grates did lovely slow cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 But they were - ooh everywhere was shining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 When was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 When was breakfast eaten - What time of the morning would you have had your breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Round about half past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well when we were all going to - when we were going to school we'd all be there for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about your father - had he had his.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Well me dad had gone to work - dad was up many a time for half past four to turn out for five o'clock. Ah well - the Carter's had to turn out t
hem days. 'Til eleven and twelve at night. And got - er - got a lousy sixpence an hour overtime. They wouldn't do it now, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How would he have had his breakfast - would your mother have got up and cooked it or would he have got it himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No, mother used to leave everything ready for him - she used to cut up of a night and leave his clean cup and saucer and - er - he was - he wasn't a good eater - but if he was going to have anything she'd - er - leave it ready for him and he'd see to i
t. If it was a bit of bacon and egg - he'd do it. And sometimes he'd just have a bit of toast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What did you usually have to eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Us at home. Well sometimes we had the old time flakes and sometimes just a bit of toast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about Sundays - would that have been any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Oh Sunday we always had a good breakfast of bacon and egg. Sometimes salt fish 'cos daddy loved a bit of fish - but - er - if any of us didn't want salt fish mum'd cook a bit of bacon and egg for us. A
nd a good roast dinner. Oooh a good roast dinner and then after dinner - while - when we'd all gone to Sunday school mum'd bake a load of cakes - currant cakes and pies for the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 So you liked Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What would you have had, give me a few examples of the kind of mid-day meal you would have had during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well, scouse and hot pot and sometimes mum'd make a pan of pea soup or you know the old time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 sheep\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  heads, well make a pan of broth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 All nice wholesome food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. All those old time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And what about puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Oh, mother used to make a rice pudding more or less every week. Yes - we always had to have - there was always the same - and sometimes she'd bake these er - currant - er - a big pudding with currants in - one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And what would you have had at tea time? When you came home from school or supper time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well when we came home at tea time - er - it was generally an egg and, or perhaps only a bit of coast but we always had a cup o
f milk and - mother used to call it a buttie - she never let us go to bed without we had that warm drink of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 But would you have said you mainly had a cooked tea or not? Would you have had an egg very often for tea or would you probably not have h
ad a cooked meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Oh well sometimes if there was any scouse or anything left from dinner time Mum'd fry it and that and share it between us. But she always see to it we had a good dinner dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 So she didn't worry too much about the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, no, we weren't going short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your mother or father ever bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, my mother baked all her own bread. Yes - we never had a bought loaf until the late years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did she make her own jam or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 She used to - no - er - onions - pickled onions - every Christmas she used to make three big jars full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 But she didn't make jam or .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did she make any wine or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - when you say medicine - s
he seen to it that every Saturday morning while we were going to school we had a dose of liquorice powder. We had that all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Didn't you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - I didn't. It was always the same - everyone - now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 you\rquote re}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  not going to drink that tea until you've had that liquorice powder. Oh dear, dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Was any beer brewed for the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. We had no way of doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did they buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No - well - well - when you say tinned fruit - mum'd get - er - as Christmas come round we always get a tin - couple of tins of fruit in what they call a club and that you know - she - she - and she always seen to it - as l
ong as ever I can remember - there was either a goose or a turkey for Christmas Day's dinner - always. She was always in a club for it - she worked that way - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did they keep any livestock for the family such as hens, pigs and goats in the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How many times a week did you eat meat? Fresh meat or tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Never had no tinned meat. Well I should think we had er - I should think we had meat more or less nearly every day and - a little bit in some way or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No. No the only rabbits that mother got was when she was in the club for Christmas time - and she bought them in the club - bought them in the club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 She often done that as long as we had it when dad wasn't doing much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 You saw her having less than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Less than us - oh yes. As long as we had it she was quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your father have more - do you ever remember your father having more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - he just always had the same but as long as mother could see him alright for going to his work - well - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 That was what she was concerned with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. That was her main .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were you allowed to talk during meals, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. We had to sit quiet over the tea table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. What mother put before us we had to eat - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well, dad was very vexed and he'd say put }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 it away}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  'til the next meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And would you have to eat it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 If there was somet
hing on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No - if - if - er - we wanted - if we wanted a bit of salt or anything we could say, mummy could we have the salt please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh I don't know about that - I can't remember - don't remember us asking for a second helping - we was - er - sufficient with the first.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And were you expected to hold the knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well, no - once we were taught to sit at the table with our knives and forks we never changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. Not over the meal - not at meal times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
When we'd all finished. And then we had to say, please mummy can I leave the table and mum would say "yes." "Yes if you've had enough", she'd say and "you can leave the table."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal, when you were all in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. We all sat together - all sat together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you always have the same place at table or did you change your seats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. We all had our own place - it was a big round table and we all sat at the one place. Always went to our own place - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How was the meal served? By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And how would she serve it - straight from the saucepans onto the plates or put it into serving dishes and put it on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No she used to - er - the meals were
 cooked in the back kitchen and when it was ready she'd put it on the plates and bring it into the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Dish it out on separate plates and bring it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes. Yes and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Who was served first when the meal was served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 He was always served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Dad - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And then the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Then all round - just - used to give us all round as we sat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And herself last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Before they could feed themselves? Where did they sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did they sit at the table with you or were they fed before on someone's knee? Can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 I can't really. No I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Can you remember them when they were very tiny being put on cushions or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 high}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  chairs or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes she was - she was very very sociable and although I'm I - well of course she's gone, she won't know, she was very well liked -
 and no matter what went wrong in the street - if anybody died - go tell Mrs. Burrows and she'll lend you the sheets. Yes she was very, very well liked - my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you find her an easy person to talk to - did you personally find her an easy person }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1139200\charrsid3944883 to talk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh yes - yes as I grew older - yes. I could tell her anything - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh yes - to everyone of use - she .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How did she show it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well she never let us go to our bed without she
 hugged us and give us a goodnight kiss and tucked us in and then she'd say 'now you're all right now then' what was it the little prayer she taught us to say - "And now I lay me down to sleep I pray thee lord my soul to keep. If I should die before I wak
e, I pray thee lord my soul to take." And we had to say that every night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
If you had any worries could you share them with her or not - if you had anything bothering you as a child - could you have shared these worries with your mother or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well - I never had none. You could do - I don't remember ever having any worries. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about your father - was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 He was very good - me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did he show affection too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 He was the same. We all had to go to him 'goodnight daddy' and he always used to stroke our heads 'God bless, goodnight'. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Could you go to your father if you had any worries that you wanted to talk to him about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well I don't know really - I never ever - er - never ever went that far really. Not as I remember, Mrs Hoskinson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well when they told you to do a thing you had to do it, that was it - well that was all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
