\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about mourning clothes - what kind of clothes would the people have worn who came to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 They went in black them days - all black - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 When you were little when you were at school were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, not often. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were you ever taken out to see friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Very rare. Dad used to take us for a walk - I re
member he - I do remember as - er - as old as I am - I remember he brought us up here - out to Speke for a run from Waltonbrech Road. But with mother and father and the family and we thought we'd had a good day then. Ooh we thought we'd gone to heaven ver
y near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were you taken shopping at all by either parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Mother used to take me perhaps me with her to help her carry the things, or perhaps she'd take Cissie, the next girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you ever go out with just your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15687279\charrsid3944883 I only taken onc
e - I was taken once to me - with me father to see his brother that was at Aintree, and of course he was - a snob because he was well off - he was better off than my poor dad - plenty of money, but - er - dad - dad - he used - er - he was in the cooperage
 in Bennets in Old Oil Street, Bill was, and he - his wife had plenty of money - well he used to work at the central cartage as well and he met dad one time and he said - he's talking to him and he said 'How's the twins going on Jack.' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Me dad said 'fine'. So he said 'never seen these twins yet'. And me dad said 'well I'll bring em along on Sunday and let you see 'em'. And dad took me and Jack along to see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you remember any other outings with your parents on bank holidays and things like that? Did you ever go anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. No, we never went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Yes. I went - the first holiday I went - went away was - my mother had a sister - and she lived in Widnes, out with Appleton way, and we went, we went - 
er - to - er - stay there one summer and there was - Jack and I and Cissie and Richard. No, Jack and I, Bill and Cissie - Richard wasn't born. That's the only time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How long would you have gone for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 We for - er - three weeks. We went for three weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And what sort of things did you do when you went?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 We went on the - well there was nothing to do there - it was a collier place. The wasn't nothing outstanding there to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 How did you spend Saturdays in those days, in those school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh just knocking round the house and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Anything different that you did on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about Sundays? Did you have different clothes to wear on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, we had special clothes, we daren't put on - daren'
t put what we had on in the week on a Sunday - and once we had 'em on Sunday well we daren't put them on in the week. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your parents think it wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 I went - no - we went to church - no we went to church three times of a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And what about playing out - did your parents think it wrong or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well they didn't let us go out to play of a Sunday - we just played in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, yes. My father .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What happened in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Mother done the dinner - mother cooked the dinner and - er - course we'd been to church - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Your mother stayed behind to cook the dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And your father didn't come with you to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Not always - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And in the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Oh he went - as - er - as the years - as the years passed on he did start to go to a Bible Class - in the - on a Sunday afternoon and then he started to go to Church of
 a Sunday night and after that again he started to go Sunday morning. Well I said to him one time, I said, 'If you're going to Church mums going to' So she said 'What about the dinner? 'I'll see to the dinner for a change, now you go to church' And my sis
ter and I done the dinner while they went to church. Well they went to church for years. Oh I was glad because it was good to see them smiling. It was good for dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What denomination was it? You say in the evening you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, yes. Presbyterian. At the top of the valley. Do you know it? No?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were there ever any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes - a Sunday school treat once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And what would that have been, what would you have done for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh well we - er - we met for - roun
d about - er - eleven o'clock then when we got to the place we used to go to Woolton, Hailward or Side Farm, Wallasey - er Magaul, Sefton Meadows and when we got there we'd get a bun and a drink of milk and then we'd have games then we had our tea. And th
en we had games again and then home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And this was once a year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Once a year. Er - about every July round about the 9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  or 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883  of July. Just as the school broke up. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What other social activities organised by this Presbyterian church did you take part in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, well, - er - yes, I was in the choir there, yes, and I was leader of the Christian Endeavour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, this is whilst you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh no after - this was later on - this was when I was about eighteen - between eighteen and twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 But you were in the choir whilst you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 But I was in the choir - oh yes, I was in the choir while I was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were there any activities concerning the choir that you used to join in apart from the obvious ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
No, we could go to er - we could go to what you call the Band of Hope and that was teaching us to keep off drink - well we could go to that once a week. That was all - while we was at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Was that a sort of temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, that's right, that's right - what they call the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And you were a member of that before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Oh yes, before I left school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And did they have any activities apart from going to the meetings that you went to once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well - er - no - well we didn't go to any of them you see, no wasn't - dad wouldn't let use - we weren't old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Was your father a member of the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 And who would say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, I told you the prayer we said.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 That particular one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you ever have family prayers together or were you told to say these to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, just at night when we went to bed mum said that prayer for us and that was it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you know what his views were - do you know what he felt - what his feelings were on this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 
Well - er - no, I don't really, he never seemed to bother about anything in any line like that - just - as long as dad had his smoke and a job to go to he was happy. Long as he was working for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 What about your mother - did she have an interest in politics? Do you know what her views were - if she had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well - er - they were - we were - we were all on the Conservative line that was - that was more so than anything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you remember your mother and father voting in a general election before 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, Conservative - always voted Conservative - yes. And I always done the same - followed them - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you remember your parents talking about any issues or if they h
ad any views about who should govern the country. You said they had Conservative points of view - so they felt that they should govern the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Well they just used to follow - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Did you ever hear them talking about whether they thought th
e working man had a square deal or not - did you ever hear them discussing that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 No, well of course, dad's dead many years now, you see, it's a long time, yes. Yes he's dead over forty years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629639 KW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid224677 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4986173\charrsid3944883 Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure - to vote for a particular party?
